---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE_NAME } from "../consts";
---

<Base title={`${SITE_NAME} for Institutions`}>
	<section class="hero">
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/institutions.png"
			alt="Institutions sharing knowledge with the public"
		/>
		<div>
			<h1>Institutions bring knowledge to the public. ReaderPub scales it.</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				A single platform for institutions publishing and sharing trusted reading.<br />
				ReaderPub supports the full institutional spectrum with tailored experiences.
			</p>
			<div class="cta-row">
				<a class="button" href="/contact">Plan an institutional pilot</a>
				<a class="button secondary" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="split">
		<div class="section">
			<h2>Publishers grow reach without losing control.</h2>
			<p>Launch catalogs, previews, and programs on a public platform built for discovery.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Control access by channel or program.</li>
				<li>Track engagement across titles.</li>
				<li>Showcase frontlist and backlist with confidence.</li>
				<li>Offer public previews or private access by segment.</li>
				<li>Measure engagement and demand by title.</li>
				<li>Build direct relationships with readers and institutions.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Sell and rent titles with lower fees — and keep your audience.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Commerce-ready distribution: sales + rentals.</li>
				<li>Low 5% commission: far below Amazon.</li>
				<li>First-party analytics: revenue, rentals, cohorts, engagement.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Add fan clubs to drive repeat demand across authors and series.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Book- and author-level memberships with direct reader access.</li>
				<li>Campaign-ready drops: releases, previews, limited access, rentals.</li>
				<li>Community analytics connected to sales and rentals.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				In addition to web publishing, ReaderPub can deliver a production-ready EPUB for
				external distribution and archiving.
			</p>
		</div>
		<img
			class="image-block image-publishers-xl"
			src="/images/publishers.png"
			alt="Publishers publishing and distributing content on ReaderPub"
		/>
	</section>

	<section class="split">
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/libraries.png"
			alt="Libraries extending public access through digital reading rooms"
		/>
		<div class="section">
			<h2>Libraries extend their mission into the public web.</h2>
			<p>Create digital reading rooms that serve patrons, partners, and communities.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Extend collections with digital programs and access..</li>
				<li>Run reading programs with impact.</li>
				<li>Curate shelves and programs with public visibility.</li>
				<li>Support community reading initiatives and cohorts.</li>
				<li>Extend collections with modern web access.</li>
				<li>Track engagement to guide programming.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="split">
		<div class="section">
			<h2>Universities publish research with visibility and trust.</h2>
			<p>Support faculty, labs, and students with a public research library.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Power coursework and cohort reading.</li>
				<li>Unify campus libraries and labs.</li>
				<li>Release working papers, reports, and open archives.</li>
				<li>Power coursework reading and cohort programs.</li>
				<li>Unify campus libraries and departmental collections.</li>
				<li>Highlight institutional expertise to the public.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/universities.png"
			alt="Universities publishing research and academic work through a public platform"
		/>
	</section>

	<section class="split">
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/government.png"
			alt="Government publishing and public access"
		/>
		<div class="section">
			<h2>Government publishes with transparency and reach.</h2>
			<p>Make public documents, research, and policy libraries easy to find and read.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Improve transparency and access.</li>
				<li>Serve staff and constituents together.</li>
				<li>Centralize reports, regulations, and public resources.</li>
				<li>Serve staff and constituents with the same library.</li>
				<li>Improve transparency with accessible reading formats.</li>
				<li>Track public engagement to inform policy work.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="split">
		<div class="section">
			<h2>Public organizations amplify mission-driven knowledge.</h2>
			<p>Publish reports, guides, and resources that reach the right communities.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Share mission resources with clarity and permanence.</li>
				<li>Curate resources for communities and partners.</li>
				<li>Publish reports with lasting visibility.</li>
				<li>Curate collections for partners and constituents.</li>
				<li>Launch public reading programs and campaigns.</li>
				<li>Build trust with transparent, accessible publishing.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/public.png"
			alt="Public organizations amplifying mission-driven knowledge"
		/>
	</section>
</Base>
